This is a default column.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong id="intable-ar-list-client">Client</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">The client of the last order placed by the contact with open claims is displayed.<br>
This is a default column.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong id="intable-ar-list-last-order">Last order</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">The date of the last order placed by the contact with open claims is displayed. <br>
This is a default column.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong id="intable-ar-list-number-accounts-receivable">Accounts receivable</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">The number of unpaid orders of the contact with open claims is displayed.<br>
This is a default column.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong id="intable-ar-list-pending-amount">Pending amount</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">The total pending amount of the contact is displayed. If a contact has overpaid an outstanding claim, this amount is offset against other outstanding claims. If no further outstanding claims exist, a deficit is displayed in the <strong>Pending amount</strong> column.<br>
This is a default column.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong id="intable-ar-list-customer-class">Customer class</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">The customer class of the contact with open claims is displayed.<br>
This is not a default column.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong id="intable-ar-list-rating">Customer rating</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">The customer rating of the contact with open claims is displayed.<br>
This is not a default column.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong id="intable-ar-list-country">Country</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">The country of the invoice address of the contact with open claims is displayed.<br>
This is not a default column.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Action</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Different actions are available to you in this column. By clicking on <span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-external-link  "></i></span>, you get redirected to the order overview in the <strong>Orders » Edit orders</strong> menu. There, a filtered view is displayed. Because of this, you directly see the unpaid and partially paid, not cancelled orders of the corresponding customer.<br>
By clicking on <span class="icon "><i class="material-message"></i></span>, you are redirected to the <strong>Messenger</strong> area in the contact data record of the customer you selected.<br>
This is a default column.</p></td>
</tr>
